{"questionId":"9076754","questionHtml":"<p>Show that the speed <em>v </em>of an electron in the hydrogen atom is related to the&nbsp;radius <em>r </em>of the orbit by the expression</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage mjpage__block\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\" alttext=\"v = \\sqrt {\\frac{{k{e^2}}}{{{m_{\\text{e}}}r}}} \">\n  <mi>v</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi>k</mi>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>e</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>m</mi>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>e</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>r</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>where <em>k </em>is the Coulomb constant.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{m_{\\text{e}}}{v^2}}}{r} = \\frac{{k{e^2}}}{{{r^2}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>m</mi>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>e</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>v</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>r</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>r</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><strong><em>OR</em></strong></p>\n<p>KE =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>PE hence <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span><em>m</em><sub>e</sub><em>v</em><sup>2</sup> =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{2}\\frac{{k{e^2}}}{r}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>r</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><strong>«</strong>solving for <em>v </em>to get answer<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Answer given – look for correct working</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[1 mark]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076754","referenceCode":"18M.2.HL.TZ2.c.i","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Show that the speed v of an electron in the hydrogen atom is related to the radius r of the orbit by the expression v = k e 2 m e r where k is the Coulomb constant.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 6: Circular motion and gravitation","6.1 – Circular motion","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism","5.1 – Electric fields","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism","Core","Topic 6: Circular motion and gravitation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}